I found a druid and he sowed me for the hefty price of 5 plat. On to Kith I go. I come to the entrance<br>
and see a bunch of people sitting there. Hahah losers, to scared to venture into the depths of Kith,<br>
and they 20 seasons above me. Well I take off running, don't want to lose my SoW in the middle of<br>
my trip. Suddenly, hit for 362 damage!! Gasp must run!!! AHHHH!!! HELP RISEN COMMANDER ON MY <br>
ARSE!!! Doh, dead. Greldek shouts to his guild, Damnit will someone come clear this spawn for me?!!?<br>
A fellow guild member replies, which spawn would that be? Greldek shouts to guild,&quot;Kithicor!&quot;.<br>
&quot;Heheh good luck. Where did you die?&quot;<br>
&quot;Oh.. somewhere in the middle I think.&quot; <br>
about 20 guild members reply with, LOL idot <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
So I run back to Kithicor and shout, &quot;Any one wanna pull my corpse for 50 plat?&quot; Got a tell from a <br>
necro, and said he'd do it, since he was right by my body anyways. It was then and there, that I <br>
decided I'm gonna hafta show those unead of kithicor who the boss really is.... in about 30 levels.<br>
Heheh Imma stupid rogue <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Greldek Draegonbayte                                         "Life is short and hard like a body building elf." -Bloodhound Gang</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub2.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=xiledpendragoran>Xiled Pendragoran</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local Rogue</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/10/00 6:01:31 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/aalanea/Xiled.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My adventure in Kithicor.</span><hr size=1> lol idiot=) <p>http://members.aol.com/aalanea/Xiled.gif</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub2.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=bayler>Bayler</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local Rogue</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/10/00 6:22:42 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My adventure in Kithicor.</span><hr size=1> It used to be fairly safe running along the walls.  Recently I've seen groups of stationary mobs hanging out in spots there, though.<br>
<br>
Just curious - are there things in Kith that can see through our hide?  I've always assumed that if I don't mind the pace, I'll be safe sneak/hiding through. <p><B>Bayler</B><BR>
18th Season Scout of Tunare<BR>
Grandmaster Fletcher<BR>
<I>Povar server</I></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub2.ezboard.com/ugreldek.showPublicProfile>Greldek</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global Rogue</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/10/00 8:55:00 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My adventure in Kithicor.</span><hr size=1> Yes the caster things see through hide. I learned that they hard way. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
I spend alot of time losing levels in Kith. Kinda sad really <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Greldek Draegonbayte                                         "Life is short and hard like a body building elf." -Bloodhound Gang</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub2.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=windup>windup</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local Rogue</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/23/00 3:58:13 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My adventure in Kithicor.</span><hr size=1> Safe pasage though Kithicor is basicly a lotto from my experience. I have used a tactic several times now that seems to work. Some players will follow a fool into kithicor using them as an early warning system for kos npc's. When i was a wee pup I led several of these PC trains. I ussually died, and they lived. Recently I decided to turn the tables on a few of these PC trains and use my guile (all of these were wall runs to wc btw). So up over a crest. num lock, hide, sneak. WOOSH the train (ussualy just 1 or 2 players). Then unhide, unsneak, numlock. The nice thing about the nasty undead kos in this area is rarely will a PC be able to make it to a zone. I would hate a backwash of these.<br>
<br>
PS: I don't ussualy go at night, unless I need to log soon, and it's a corpse retrieval.<br>
<br>
Windup<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upedriccuf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pedric Cuf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/7/01 4:54:14 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My adventure in Kithicor.</span><hr size=1> Hmmm. I stuck to the path and I traversed the whole thing at night while sneaking and hiding. Slow going but I assume that if you keep moving that they won't aggro on you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uharryh0od.showPublicProfile?language=EN>harryh0od</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/17/01 10:46:29 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My adventure in Kithicor.</span><hr size=1> There is also a nasty DE rogue in there that sees through s/h. When I came across him it was day time and was red to me at 30. I got lucky and he missed his BS, woot!<br>
<br>
 -harryh0od <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ustytchyapgud.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stytch Yapgud</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/18/01 6:19:39 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My adventure in Kithicor.</span><hr size=1> Stick to the wall with sneak an hide an you should be ok even at night. Least I allways have though I havnt done the journey in about a month so not sure if the spawn spots have changed.<br>
<br>
